Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:09.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,[历史频道] 第二季 第十集 星座\N[History Channel] The UniverseⅡ 10of19 Constellations
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:11.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,自互联网和电影问世之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before the lnternet, before movies...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.65,0:01:13.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,夜空和星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the night sky and the constellations...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.69,0:01:18.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是最有看头的表演\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were the greatest show in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.16,0:01:22.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个群星画廊远胜过美丽的图画\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This gallery of stars forms more thanjust pretty pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.79,0:01:26.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它包括了各类星星的巨大采样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt contains an enormous sampling of star types.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:28.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Through constellations...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.50,0:01:33.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以认识星系乃至宇宙的很多东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can learn a lot about the galaxy...and the universe beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.55,0:01:39.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们的高科技导航设备GPS乃至罗盘问世之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before we had high-tech navigation devices...GPS, or even compasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.43,0:01:41.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就有了星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we had stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.97,0:01:44.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宛如路标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like landmarks along the road...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.52,0:01:47.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星座能帮助我们找路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}constellations can help us find our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:49.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们给了我们方向 距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They give us direction, distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.15,0:01:52.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和目标感\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a sense of where to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.48,0:01:54.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地球上我们想说出东西的位置时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So on Earth, when we want to tell where something is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.65,0:01:58.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会给出其经纬度坐标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we give its coordinates in latitude and longitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:01:59.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上所表示的意思是一种尺度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what that means on Earth is a measure of...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.66,0:02:05.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,纬度就是南北极之间距离的尺度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}latitude is a measure of the distance...between the North Pole and the South Pole...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.62,0:02:10.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而经度则是另一个方向 东西距离的尺度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and longitude is the east-west distance...from the other direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:14.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样 我们也有一个星空坐标系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Similarly, we have a celestial coordinate system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.09,0:02:15.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而这个坐标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the coordinates...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.34,0:02:17.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并不叫做纬度和经度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're not called latitude and longitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:20.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是叫做赤纬和赤经\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're called declination and right ascension.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.05,0:02:23.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们只是地球的经纬度直接延展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are just the direct extensions...of latitude and longitude on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.68,0:02:26.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,投射到空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}projected out into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.35,0:02:29.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,古代航海家利用这个虚构的网格\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ancient navigators used this imaginary grid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:32.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来划分群星并引领他们飘洋过海\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to plot stars and orient themselves across the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.94,0:02:35.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不是那种精准的方向指示器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not a precise kind of indicator of direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:39.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但无疑是一个指示 提醒人们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but certainly a cue to keep people reminded...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.78,0:02:44.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,越洋通道的模样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what the broad pathways through the seas might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.20,0:02:45.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,依靠六分仪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By using a sextant...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:50.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,船员能够利用北极星之类的引路星来导航\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mariners were able to use guide stars like Polaris...to navigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:51.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是架六分仪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is a sextant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.67,0:02:54.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是天文导航的工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a tool used in celestial navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.67,0:02:55.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦 一个天体对准了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once a celestial body hits...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.88,0:02:58.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个所谓的水平度盘的下翼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what's called this lower limb to the horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.63,0:03:00.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就标记其位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we mark the position.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.84,0:03:04.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,利用六分仪上的刻度和数字\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using the time and the numbers on this sextant...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:07.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就可以用它来定位你在海上的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can then use it in fixing your position at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.64,0:03:12.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在导航利用人造星:卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today's navigation uses manmade stars: satellites.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.56,0:03:15.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,利用卫星本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With the use of our manmade stars per se...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.32,0:03:18.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们GPS的位置 导航差分GPS\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our GPS positions and differential GPS...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.36,0:03:24.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就能够在世界各地立马定位船只在数码之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're able to fix the ship's position...within a fewyards instantaneously...anywhere we are in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:27.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在GPS已取代了六分仪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now that GPS has replaced sextants...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.58,0:03:30.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天体坐标对天文学家的重要性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}celestial coordinates are more important to astronomers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:33.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就超过了海员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than they are to sailors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.04,0:03:36.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使坐标系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even though the coordinate system...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.59,0:03:39.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能给他们望远镜指向的主意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gives them an idea of where to point their telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.63,0:03:42.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 坐标还是达不到精准的地步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the grid falls short in a serious way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:44.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它假设所有的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt assumes all the stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.01,0:03:47.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,距离我们都一样远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are all the same distance from us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:50.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个大错特错的假设\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an assumption that's flat-out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.35,0:03:54.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看夜空中的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you look at the stars in the night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.44,0:03:57.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们似乎都差不多远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they all appear to be about the same distance away...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.52,0:04:00.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,仿佛在同一个平面上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as if they were in the same plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.36,0:04:04.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样的情况发生在你从远处看城市的轮廓线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same happens when you look at a city skyline...from a distance away...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.74,0:04:07.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如我们看芝加哥的轮廓线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as we are from the Chicago skyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.49,0:04:08.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,整个那些建筑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So while those buildings...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.95,0:04:10.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看上去好像都一样远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}look like they're the same distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:13.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上 它们是在距离非常不同的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're really at many different distances away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.46,0:04:14.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,群星同样如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same is true of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:16.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然 它们看上去好像在相同的距离上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While they all look like they're at the same distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:20.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 有些近些 有些要远很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some are close, some are much further away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.05,0:04:22.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么 我们是如何知道哪些星近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So how do we know which stars are close...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.72,0:04:25.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,哪些星远的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and which are far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.22,0:04:30.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是我们现在感觉最难的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it turns out...that's the most difficult question of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.72,0:04:37.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这一直是整个天文学里 一个最棘手的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's been the single greatest frustration...in all of astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.48,0:04:39.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察夜空 即便使用上了望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Looking at the night sky, even with telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.94,0:04:43.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你都无法辨别距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you cannot tell distances.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.32,0:04:47.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是数百年里天文学的圣杯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's been the holy grail of astronomy for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.12,0:04:54.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们现在来到了安琪拉国家森林公园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're here in the Angeles National Forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.83,0:04:57.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我带着便携旅游地图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and l've got with me a handy trail map.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:58.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我想徒步旅行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And l'd like to take a hike...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.67,0:05:00.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能会去斯维泽瀑布\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe going to, say, Switzer Falls...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:04.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这在地图上 看上去好像并不太远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which, on my map, looks like it's not very far...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.42,0:05:05.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能只有1英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only maybe a mile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:13.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我可能严重低估了这个徒步旅行的困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the trouble is...l could badly underestimate the difficulty of this hike...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:16.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我的平面地图没有考虑到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because my flat map here fails to take into account...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:21.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个非常重要的因素 海拔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one very significant factor, which is the elevation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.61,0:05:25.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 事实上 我简单的一英里徒步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, in fact, my simple one-mile hike...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:27.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,结果成了5000英尺的爬山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could turn out to be a 5,000-foot climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.53,0:05:33.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样 我的星座地图也未能告诉我\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So does my constellation map fail to tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.16,0:05:35.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两颗星之间的真实距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about the true distance between two stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:37.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使是在一个星座里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though in a constellation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.29,0:05:39.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能看上去它们相互紧挨着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they might look like they're right next to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:42.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但事实上 一颗可能会比另一颗远很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in fact, one could be much farther away than the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.21,0:05:44.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,加入我光看天文坐标的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and l would never know it if l just looked...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.46,0:05:47.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就永远不知晓了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the celestial coordinates only.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:51.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和森林里的徒步者一样 天文学家依靠线索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like hikers in the woods, astronomers rely on clues...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.14,0:05:56.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来帮助自己判断我们巨大而神秘的宇宙中的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to help them gauge the distances...in our vast and mysterious universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:57.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 我们在森林里行走时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, when we're hiking in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.85,0:06:00.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使我们没有能告诉海拔的地图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even if we don't have a map that tells us elevation...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.23,0:06:03.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们也能利用当地地形学和树木分类的知识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can use our knowledge of the local topography...and types of trees...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.78,0:06:06.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来告诉我们海拔的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to tell us something about our altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.07,0:06:08.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如有些树适应低海拔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, certain trees prefer lower elevation...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.86,0:06:11.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而其它树则是应高海拔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whereas other trees prefer higher altitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.70,0:06:15.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样天文学家利用某类定标星作为路标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Similarly, astronomers use...certain types of reference stars as guideposts...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.87,0:06:20.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非正式的路标 作为距离的尺度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}familiar guideposts, as a gauge of distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.71,0:06:22.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家工具包里第一件工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first tool in the astronomer's kit...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:25.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是视差现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the phenomenon of parallax.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.01,0:06:29.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这东西我们每天用来在小尺度上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's something we use on a smaller scale every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.18,0:06:33.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察三维世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see the world in three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.85,0:06:35.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个方法被认为视差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The way to think of parallax...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.39,0:06:39.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是每个人都能做的非常简单的练习\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a very simple exercise that everybody can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:41.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看着你的手指\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take a look at yourfinger...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:44.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看着很远的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and look at something really, really far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.90,0:06:46.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你用上右眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf you use your right eye...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.23,0:06:49.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把你的手指对准远方的目标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and line up yourfinger with a distant object...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.11,0:06:50.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后用上你的左眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then use your left eye...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.61,0:06:53.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就会看到你的手指实际上表现出移动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll see that yourfinger actually appears to move...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.53,0:06:56.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相当戏剧性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}quite dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.49,0:06:58.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成这种移动的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This apparent shif t is caused...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.16,0:07:02.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是我们两眼之间的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the distance between our two eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:03.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家测量视差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers measure parallax...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:08.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是通过在一个位置上观察星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by looking at a star at one position...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:12.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后六个月后再来观察它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then looking at it again six months later...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.09,0:07:15.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那时它已经移到了距离我们观察点尽可能远的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it's moved as far as it could go...from our vantage point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:21.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,六个月 其实是地球尽可能远离原始位置的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Six months is really when the Earth is as far away...from that original position as it can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:30.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星星越近视差就越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The closer the star, the greater the parallax.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:35.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,问题是星星都不是很近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem is that stars aren't very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.24,0:07:38.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至我们最近的星星 比邻星的视差角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the parallax angle of our closest star...Proxima Centauri,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.20,0:07:43.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都很难测出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is difficult to measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.83,0:07:46.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它小于一秒弧度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's less than a second of arc.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.13,0:07:47.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一秒弧度是什么概念？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's a second of arc?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.34,0:07:49.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,圆周是360度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's 360 degrees in a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.01,0:07:55.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每度又有60分弧度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln every degree, there is 60 minutes of arc.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.26,0:08:00.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每分弧度又有60秒弧度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in every minute of arc, there are 60 seconds of arc.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:05.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比邻星是0.7秒弧度的视差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Proxima Centauri has a parallax of 0.7 seconds of arc...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.94,0:08:08.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以非常的小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it's very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.90,0:08:11.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于更为遥远的星星的跨距\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To span the distance to more far-flung stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.28,0:08:16.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家依靠一种熟悉的路标来指引\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers count on...a familiar guidepost to lead them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.20,0:08:21.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像海岸警卫队利用灯塔一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much like the Coast Guard uses a lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.12,0:08:23.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海岸警卫队人人都知道每一座灯塔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The men and women of the Coast Guard... know that every lighthouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.71,0:08:26.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都有特定的脉冲频率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has a particular pulsation frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.42,0:08:28.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一座可能每分钟闪烁两次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One might flash two times a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.46,0:08:29.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另一座 会是4次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another, four times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.75,0:08:33.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们可以利用这个来确定自己的准确位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can use this to determine exactly their position...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.47,0:08:36.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就基于那种式样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just based on the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:37.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the same way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.35,0:08:39.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家可以利用一种宇宙灯塔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers can use a cosmic lighthouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:42.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,叫做造父变星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called a cepheid variable star.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.81,0:08:44.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,仙王座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The constellation Cepheus...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.64,0:08:47.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,取名来自埃塞俄比亚神话中的国王\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}named after the mythical king ofAetheopia...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.77,0:08:52.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,拥有57颗看得见的星星 包括仙王座δ\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}claims 57 visible stars, including Delta Cephei...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.40,0:08:58.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这颗变星是造父变星的原型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a variable star that is the prototype...for cepheid variables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:08:59.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,靠天性怪癖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By a quirk of nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.91,0:09:03.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造父变星守时如节拍器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cepheids keep time like a metronome.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:05.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造父变星越大越亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bigger and brighter the cepheid...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.79,0:09:08.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其脉动则越慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the slower it will pulsate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:11.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你要做的就是找到造父变星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what you do is find the cepheid variable...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.17,0:09:13.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,测量其脉动周期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}measure its pulsation period...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:15.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能是10天或60天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it might be 10 days or 60 days...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:19.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是你就得到了一个标准蜡烛了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then you've got a standard candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.47,0:09:24.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就可以判断那颗星有多远了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can determine howfar away that star is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.35,0:09:30.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,标准蜡烛是比较已知恒星亮度和距离的基础\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A standard candle is a basis of comparison...a star of known luminosity and distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:34.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以与类似恒星进行比对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we can compare similar stars against.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.49,0:09:36.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,灯泡发出一定量的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A light bulb gives off the amount of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.99,0:09:39.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会发出一定量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt gives off a certain amount of watts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:41.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 灯光会看上去更亮一些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that light is going to look a lot brighter...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.53,0:09:43.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只要你更加靠近灯泡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you're right up close to that light bulb...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.45,0:09:46.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而不是更远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than if you are ten feet away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.41,0:09:50.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 星星的亮度并没有变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so the luminosity of a star doesn't change...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.50,0:09:52.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 就是那回事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you know, that is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.17,0:09:54.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 星星亮度等级的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But apparent magnitude, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.34,0:09:58.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,却是取决于你所处的位置 你有多远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depends on where you are, howfar away you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.22,0:10:00.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管你是距离物体近呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whetheryou're right up close to something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.14,0:10:04.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还是在街的另一头看它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or you're seeing it from the other side of the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:07.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果 造父变星并不是很亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf a cepheid doesn't appear that bright...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.39,0:10:10.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那它必定很遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then it must be far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:17.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家们可以基于其的亮度来计算出它有多远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers can calculate howfar it is...based on how dim it appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.40,0:10:21.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看着我的造父变星病绘制出其光变曲线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Looking at my cepheid variable and plotting the light curve...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:26.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从亮到暗 再到亮有多长时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how long it takes to go from brightness to dim...and back to brightness again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.70,0:10:31.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就可以得出那颗星的内在亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tells me what the intrinsic brightness of that star is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.25,0:10:34.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这样我就可以通过观察它们的变动周期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So l can calculate distance to variable stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:37.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来计算出变星的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by observing the period of their variation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.01,0:10:40.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,埃德温·哈勃就是用这个方法测定了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's how Edwin Hubble was able to determine...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:47.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,仙女座在我们银河系外面200万光年的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thatAndromeda was two million light-years...outside our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.27,0:10:49.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 造父变星有自己的局限\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But cepheid variables have their limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:52.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要测量仙女座以外的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To measure distances far beyond Andromeda...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.44,0:10:55.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家则要依靠超新星了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers rely on supernovas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.53,0:11:06.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,原来超新星也可以归类为标准蜡烛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt turns out that supernovae can also be categorized...as standard candles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:10.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,整个宇宙间的1A型超新星都是一模一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Type 1a supernovae are all the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.21,0:11:11.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们掌握了测定它们的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know how to calibrate them...throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:19.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是 如何测定与大爆炸以及宇宙边缘的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's how we determine the distances...out to the Big Bang...and the very edges of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:21.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,深入大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Peering into the Big Bang...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.97,0:11:26.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家几乎能看到时间的起点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists can nearly see the beginning of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.85,0:11:31.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大爆炸后30万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}300,000 years after the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.14,0:11:33.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使我们最熟悉的星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even our most familiar constellations...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:36.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也有许多关于宇宙的东西教给我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have a lot to teach us about the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.19,0:11:41.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,猎户(座) 希腊人对猎人的称呼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Orion, which is Greek for hunter...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.61,0:11:45.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有77颗可见的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has 77 visible stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.53,0:11:49.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,参宿一 参宿二和参宿三\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Alnitak, Alnilam, and Mintaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.33,0:11:53.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,组成了猎户腰带三星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}make up the three stars in Orion's belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.42,0:11:56.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现代 天文学家搜索猎户座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln modern times, astronomers have hunted Orion...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:12:02.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现了各种惊人的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}finding a variety of astonishing objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.09,0:12:04.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我观察猎户座时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When l see Orion...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:08.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同时 也看到了星星的生死存亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l also see the life and death of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.10,0:12:09.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就在腰带下方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just below the belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.31,0:12:12.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有一个斑点 叫做猎户座星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's a little smudge called the Orion Nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.06,0:12:15.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是个托儿所 初生星犊的托儿所\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, that's a nursery, a nursery for baby stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.69,0:12:19.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上你可以肉眼看到它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you can actually see that with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:24.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,猎户囊中还有一对恒星宝石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Orion has also bagged a pair of stellar gems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.95,0:12:26.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看猎户的左肩上方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf you look at the upper left-hand shoulder of Orion...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.03,0:12:29.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以看到一颗红色的巨星 参宿四\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you see the red giant Betelgeuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.41,0:12:30.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你径直往下看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if you immediately look right down...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.04,0:12:32.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,右下方的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the lower right star...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.87,0:12:34.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是他腿上的那颗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star that's sort of his leg...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.75,0:12:38.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就可以看到一颗蓝色的超级巨星 参宿七\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll see the blue supergiant Rigel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.21,0:12:41.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,参宿四 红色超级巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse, as a red supergiant...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:45.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是颗垂死挣扎的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a star in its death throes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.76,0:12:50.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,红色超级巨星实际上温度比太阳低很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A red supergiant is a star...that is actually quite a bit cooler than our Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.26,0:12:51.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 却要大很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but much, much larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.64,0:12:56.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,参宿四的质量比太阳大14倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse is14 times more massive than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:12:58.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦用完核燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it runs out of nuclear fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:13:00.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,参宿四将会变得不稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse will become unstable...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:04.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,向内聚爆成一颗巨大的超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and implode in a colossal supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:07.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它随时都会爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt can detonate at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:08.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它爆发时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when it explodes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.74,0:13:11.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将会点亮整个夜空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will light up the entire night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.54,0:13:15.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至在白天都看得到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it will even be visible during daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.71,0:13:17.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许它已经爆发了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And maybe it's already blown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:20.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它距离地球427光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's 427 light-years from Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:24.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就意味着 或许它已经爆发了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which means that perhaps it has already exploded...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:28.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但光尚未来得及抵达我们这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but light hasn't had time to reach us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:31.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星会将注意力引向数千年来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The supernova will draw more attention to a sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.43,0:13:36.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一直在吸引着我们的天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's been captivating us for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:43.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,古埃及人问天耕种收获的时计\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ancient Egyptians consulted the heavens...to tell them when to plant and when to harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:46.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每颗星都具有神圣的意义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every star possessed a sacred meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.45,0:13:47.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们叫天狼星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They called Sirius...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.99,0:13:49.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在大犬星座里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the constellation Canis Major...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.03,0:13:52.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,伊希斯女神之星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Star of lsis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.37,0:13:56.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天狼星出现在夏至时分的破晓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sirius' appearance before dawn during the summer solstice...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.37,0:14:00.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,预示着尼罗河每年的泛滥\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forecasted the annual rise of the Nile river.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.38,0:14:02.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其它星座 如猎户座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Other constellations, like Orion...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:07.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能具有某种建筑意义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might have had a certain architectural significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.59,0:14:10.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,埃及古物学者经常会提出这样的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Egyptologists have of ten asked the question...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.47,0:14:13.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为何古埃及人建造了三座大金字塔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why did the ancient Egyptians build three great pyramids...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:15.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并稍稍错位呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are slightly misaligned?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.72,0:14:18.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,难道他们在数千年前用了错误的尺子来定位的吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Did they have bad ruler sticks thousands of years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:25.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,三座金字塔看来对应着猎户座的三颗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The three pyramids seem to be aligned...to the three constellation stars of Orion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.48,0:14:28.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种排列意味着什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What does this alignment mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.32,0:14:34.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是巧合 还是金字塔有目的的以这种方式设计的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Was it a coincidence, or were the pyramids...intentionally engineered this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.87,0:14:41.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,吉萨金字塔的迷人之处在于其考古的神秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pyramids of Giza seduce us with archeological mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.29,0:14:44.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及历史的机巧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and historical intrigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.34,0:14:46.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些科学家认为金字塔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some scientists think the pyramids...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:49.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,具有一定的天文意义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have a certain astronomical importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.93,0:14:52.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,声称包括大金字塔在内的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt has been claimed that the layout...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.18,0:14:56.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,三座大金字塔在吉萨高原上的布局\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the three major pyramids on the Giza plateau...including the great pyramid...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.02,0:15:03.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是在地面上模仿猎户的腰带三星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are set on the ground...to mimic the three stars in Orion's belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.40,0:15:07.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我最喜欢的地球事件与天空事件之间的联系之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's one of my favorite connections...between events on Earth and events in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.94,0:15:09.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过古埃及人并未像我们这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the ancient Egyptians...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.53,0:15:12.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看到猎户座里的猎人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}didn't see a hunter in Orion like we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.70,0:15:17.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们看到了奥西里斯 再生之神\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They saw Osiris, God of Rebirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:20.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有人猜测大金字塔里的通风井\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some speculate that air shafts within the great pyramids...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:26.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是专门设计用来将法老的灵魂射向天堂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were specifically designed...to catapult the souls of pharaohs to the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.67,0:15:29.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在那些金字塔里我们看到了两种不同通风道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln those pyramids, we have two different shafts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.21,0:15:30.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些通风道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And those shafts...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:33.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一条往南 一条往北\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one points north and one points south.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.43,0:15:36.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,往南的通道指向猎户座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The south shaft points toward Orion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:39.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 法老的灵魂会射出井道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the soul of the pharaoh...would be launched through that shaft...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.73,0:15:43.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为了会合奥西里斯 猎户座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in order to be connected to Osiris, Orion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.02,0:15:47.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,复活 享受来世\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and be resurrected again, enjoying eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.03,0:15:50.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可其他人则表示怀疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But others are a bit more skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.57,0:15:52.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为了使其准确匹配\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln order to make it match correctly...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.66,0:15:57.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须将其倒置放到地上或空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have to flip it upside down on the ground...or in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.20,0:16:02.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是埃及人却将重点放在金字塔的南边和北边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the Egyptians did place an importance...on north and on south in the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:05.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这毫无道理可言\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it doesn't make any sense to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.08,0:16:07.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是 他们将星星排成一线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}well, yes, they lined the stars up right...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.25,0:16:09.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是在它映射到地面上时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but then when it came to mapping on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.71,0:16:12.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就完全将一切给反转了过来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was perfectly okay to flip everything around...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.13,0:16:14.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,上下倒了个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and make it upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.34,0:16:18.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,往北的通道对准了一颗特定的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The north shaft points toward one specific star.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.64,0:16:19.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,往北的那个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The one pointing north...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.77,0:16:26.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当时 公元前2000-3000年 指向了北极星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}points to the pole star at the time...2,000 years before Christ, 2000 B.C., 3000 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.44,0:16:28.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,北极星就是右枢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that pole star was Thuban.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:33.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,右枢座落在天龙星座里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thuban is located in the constellation Draco...or the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.61,0:16:37.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天龙星座有79颗可见星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Draco has 79 visible stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.74,0:16:42.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,右枢已被当代人的极星 北极星 所取代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thuban has been replaced...by our generation's pole star, Polaris.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.00,0:16:45.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,北极星照亮了北极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Polaris illuminates the arctic...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.62,0:16:50.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,像北极上方的灯塔那样控制着天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}governing our sky as a beacon over the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.80,0:16:53.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,身处小熊星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lying in the constellation Ursa Minor...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.63,0:16:57.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比太阳亮2500倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's 2,500 times brighter than the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.64,0:17:03.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,让其伴星北极星AB 及北极星B相形见绌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}outshining its companion stars Polaris AB and B.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:09.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管它有史以来一直作为北方之星统治着苍穹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although it's ruled the heavens as our north star...for as long as we can remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.15,0:17:12.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 其统治地位不会永远不倒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its reign won't last forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.65,0:17:16.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着地球围绕太阳的运转 它在来回地摆动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As Earth orbits the Sun, it teeters back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.99,0:17:20.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种摆动称为岁差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This wobbling is called precession.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.41,0:17:24.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果地球是个完美的球体 是不会进动的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf Earth was a perfect sphere, it wouldn't precess...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.46,0:17:27.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是月球与太阳的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the gravitational pulls of the Moon and Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.88,0:17:32.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,牵引隆起的赤道 扰乱着地球的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tug at the bulging equator, upsetting Earth's spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:36.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球就像陀螺仪或陀螺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the Earth is like a gyroscope or a spinning top.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:38.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,请注意 如果我快速旋转它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Notice that if l spin this very rapidly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.01,0:17:40.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我移动其轴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then l move the axis...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:42.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它指的方向不变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it points in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.02,0:17:45.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是地球指向北极星的原因所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the Earth pointing toward Polaris...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.43,0:17:47.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地球围绕太阳转动时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that as the Earth goes around the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.64,0:17:49.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它总是指向同一个方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it always points in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:53.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是岁差是引力干扰造成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, precession is caused...by gravitational interference...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:55.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 地球就开始颤动了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so the Earth begins to wobble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.03,0:17:57.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着地球的颤动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As Earth wobbles...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.95,0:18:01.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地轴在天上划出一个圆圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its axis draws a circle in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:06.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,需要2.6万年才能划出一个完整的圆圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt takes 26,000 years to make one complete circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:11.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,北天极将越来越远离北极星的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The north celestial pole...will move further and further away...from the position of Polaris.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.88,0:18:15.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在1.4万年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln about 14,000 years from now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.59,0:18:18.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其圆圈走完一半的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about halfway around its circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.38,0:18:21.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将会非常靠近亮星-织女星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will be very close to the bright star vega.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:23.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是因为织女星要比那个空域里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But because Vega is so much brighter...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.39,0:18:25.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其它星星亮很多很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than any other star in that part of the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.72,0:18:32.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它就会成为一颗非常有影响力的北极星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will be a very significant north polar star.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.77,0:18:37.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,2.6万年里 地轴 以北极为中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln 26,000 years, Earth's axis, centered on the North Pole...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.24,0:18:39.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将会走完一个完整的圆周\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will make one complete circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.57,0:18:43.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,重新指向它现在的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it will point back to where it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.83,0:18:45.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,北极星将会推翻织女星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Polaris will overthrowVega...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:50.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,夺回其北方之星的头衔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and reclaim its title as our north star.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.08,0:18:53.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星星距离地球的一极越近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The closer a star is to one of Earth's poles...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.09,0:18:56.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其停留在天上的固定位置就越久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the more its position remains fixed in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.01,0:19:00.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家称那些星为拱极星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers call these stars circumpolar...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:05.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,意思是它们常年可见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}meaning that they're visible all year long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.18,0:19:09.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 北方星空的所有星座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, all of the constellations...of northern stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:11.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如小熊座和大熊座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as the Little Dipper and the Big Dipper...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.40,0:19:14.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是绕着很小的圈子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just go around in a fairly small circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.23,0:19:15.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以其结果是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the result of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.44,0:19:19.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们围绕北极运转 没有上升和下落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they go around Polaris without ever rising and setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.07,0:19:20.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你越往南\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The further south you go...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.28,0:19:23.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,升起的星座就越多 也就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the more constellations actually rise, say...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:25.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在夜幕降临时分以及黎明到来之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the beginning of the night...and set at the end of the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.95,0:19:30.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们不具有那种魔力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so they don't have that magical property.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:36.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星星之间的差异在于个头 密度 还有亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars vary in size, density and also brightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.21,0:19:39.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不像大多数星星那样稳定发出光辉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lnstead of shining with a steady glow...like most stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.46,0:19:45.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,变星以催眠模式有规律地变化着明暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}variable stars pulsate...brightening and dimming in a hypnotic pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.43,0:19:48.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,变星就像一壶茶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A variable star is like a pot of tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.97,0:19:52.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你把茶壶放在炉子上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You take a kettle and put it on a burner...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.56,0:19:53.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它就开始膨胀了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it starts to expand...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.94,0:19:56.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后它释放出过剩的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then it releases its excess energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.32,0:19:57.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是就落下了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.52,0:19:59.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后它又开始积蓄压力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then it starts to build up pressure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.57,0:20:01.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是又落下了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then it drops again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:02.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样的道理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So kind of in the same way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.78,0:20:06.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,变星的大气层一直在膨胀收缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the variable stars' atmospheres...expand and shrink with time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.99,0:20:10.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就让变星看上去变亮变暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this makes the star appear to get brighter and dimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.33,0:20:12.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时会发生在几个小时里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes this happens over a matter of hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.25,0:20:16.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时会有几天甚至几个月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes it can be days or even months.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.13,0:20:20.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有类特殊的变星 叫做T型变星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A special class of variable stars...called T-Tauri stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.51,0:20:23.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其脉动是因为年轻不稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pulsate because they're young and unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:28.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和顽童一般 T型变星会莫名其妙地爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like stubborn teenagers, T-Tauri stars...have erratic outbursts...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.81,0:20:33.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不止是与引力抗争的突然爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}except their tantrums involve a struggle with gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:38.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于核力把它往外推\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the nuclearforces push it outward...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.36,0:20:39.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力将它往里拽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gravity pulls it back in...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.90,0:20:42.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它失去了平衡的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it misses that equilibrium position...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.11,0:20:44.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有点像钟摆来回地摆动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sort of like a pendulum...and it oscillates back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.91,0:20:52.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,T型变星的成长快于它们的脉动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}T-Tauris will outgrow their pulsations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.20,0:20:54.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着年龄增长 它们会趋于平衡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As they age, they'll reach equilibrium...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.58,0:20:57.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,成为沉稳的星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}becoming stable stars.
